  "title": "Search form that submits on click and goes to results page",
  "body": "Hey all, we need to have a search function across various pages but this time, the results won't be vibisle on the page so therefore, when submitted, the user will be taken to a results page. Has anybody achieved this?\n\nI've got the search functions in place and I've removed the hits etc so it works as expected, just finding it difficult to go off to another page and show results. Looking through many posts with similar questions, I've tried helpers and many functions but it appears that's out of my scope. \n\nInitially, I though that I could try 'getQueryUrl' as I thought this was the full query of the search on change but haven't managed to get it working. \n\nAny help would massively appreciated. Thanks!\n",
